==========VCD-Parser==========

Init: ./configure.sh
Build: 'make' inside build/
Usage: ./bin/vcd_parser --format=log|regdump|json|comment [--<filter>=<value>] <file.vcd>" <path_to_vcd_file>

Converts a VCD file to a different output formats with different textual filters.
A filter ignores all entries, which do not contain the filter-argument.

===formats===
--format=log               cycle: scope.signal <= value
--format=regdump           macsim-compare-format
--format=json              scope-structure of all signals
--format=comment           all comments in the VCD-header

===filters===
--scope=<filter>           filter scopes
--signal=<filter>          filter signals
--value=<filter>           filter values
--min-cycle=<filter>       start with cycle filter
--max-cycle=<filter>       end with cycle filter

Examples:
./bin/vcd_parser --format=regdump --scope=reg1.reg1 --signal=reg <file.vcd>
    Extract all changes in scopes containing "reg1.reg1" and there only the
    signals matching "reg". This produces the compare-format for macsim.
    
./bin/vcd_parser --format=log --value=U <file.vcd>
    Displays all signals with Undefined values. (Containing U)

